            <p>A blood gas analyzer is a critical-care instrument. If you ask <strong>what does a blood gas analyzer measure</strong>, it assesses the levels of oxygen (pO2), carbon dioxide (pCO2), pH, and bicarbonate in an arterial blood sample. When reviewing <strong>how does blood gas analyzer work</strong>, the machine utilizes highly sensitive electrochemical electrodes (glass pH electrodes, Severinghaus carbon dioxide sensors, and Clark oxygen sensors) to detect tiny electrical potential changes and calculate gas concentration values instantly.</p>
